==English==

===Etymology===
Latin "to make cold" (<[[re-]] + ''[[frigus]]'')

===Transitive verb===
{{en-verb|refrigerat|ing}}

# To cool or keep cool, typically by containing within a [[refrigerator]].
#:''Please '''refrigerate''' your uncooked meats at or below 40° Fahrenheit.''

